# neofetch

> CLI system tool to display information about your system next to an image, your OS logo, or any ASCII file of your choice.
> NOTE: Every launch flag has a config option.

- Call neofetch (if the script config file has been set up previously):

`neofetch`

- Pass specific parameters:

`neofetch --option "value" --option "value"`

- Disable an info line from appearing in the output:

`neofetch --disable infoname`

- Hide/Show OS architecture:

`neofetch --os_arch on/off`

- Enable/Disable CPU brand in output

`neofetch --cpu_brand on/off`
